<Page x:Class="AsynAwaitExamples.Steps.Step15_CpuBoundVsIoBound"
      xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
      xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
      xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:AsynAwaitExamples.ViewModels"
      Title="Step 15 - CPU vs I/O Bound">
    <Page.DataContext>
        <vm:Step15ViewModel/>
    </Page.DataContext>
    <ScrollViewer VerticalScrollBarVisibility="Auto">
        <StackPanel Margin="10">
            <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource HeaderStyle}" 
                       Text="Step 15: Task.Run - CPU-Bound vs I/O-Bound Work"/>

            <TextBlock Style="{StaticResource ExplanationStyle}" xml:space="preserve">CPU-BOUND vs I/O-BOUND: Knowing the difference determines your approach.

I/O-bound: Waiting for something external (network, disk, database).
The thread is IDLE. Just use "await" directly. No Task.Run needed.

CPU-bound: Crunching numbers, processing data, image manipulation.
The thread is BUSY. Use Task.Run to move it to a background thread.

RULE: I/O-bound = await directly. CPU-bound = await Task.Run.
Don't wrap I/O in Task.Run. That wastes a thread to just sit and wait.</TextBlock>

            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="[1] CPU-bound WITHOUT Task.Run (freezes UI)"
                    Command="{Binding CpuBoundBlockingCommand}"/>
            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="[2] CPU-bound WITH Task.Run (UI stays responsive)"
                    Command="{Binding CpuBoundWithTaskRunCommand}"/>
            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="[3] I/O-bound: just await (no Task.Run needed)"
                    Command="{Binding IoBoundCorrectCommand}"/>
            <Button Style="{StaticResource ActionButton}"
                    Content="[4] Mixed workload: CPU + I/O together"
                    Command="{Binding MixedWorkloadCommand}"/>

            <TextBox Style="{StaticResource OutputStyle}" Height="280"
                     Text="{Binding OutputText, Mode=OneWay}"/>
        </StackPanel>
    </ScrollViewer>
</Page>
